      <scopecontent id="aspace_ef47c904817e6dc02ff8e3fb9c31f9aa">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>This finding aid encompasses accessions of single manuscripts and small groups of manuscripts and other papers, by or pertaining to Hester Lynch Piozzi, which the library has chosen to group and list as an artificial collection.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
      <bioghist id="aspace_209befa4a818e525edc77db160827029">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>Hester Lynch Piozzi (1741-1821), née Salusbury, was a Welsh-born diarist, author, and patron of the arts, known for her writings on Samuel Johnson. She married London-based brewer and politician Henry Thrale in 1763, and music teacher Gabriel Mario Piozzi in 1784.</p>  
      </bioghist>
